<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98805788231758></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98805788231758><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=4341&mid=98805788231758>Killled him yesterday</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 23rd 4:31 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>We got him yesterday.  We pulled him to the part of the beach where there are no otter men.  He dropped the Cloak, 2-3 spells, 2 9/20 rogue piercers, a scale, and a bioluminescent orb.  Not bad.<br><br>He did not fear anyone.  He did not hit exceptionally hard.  He seems to have a cold based area effect.  Sometimes it hit me for 100, other times it hit for 1000.  Overall, he is not a tough kill.  I think 2 groups of 60's with good group balance could take him.  You may want to bring 4, just to be safe.<br><br>The haste on the cloak is 36%.  It matched my Cloak of Flames.  Personally, I'll take the CoF.  The extra hitpoints do more for a TSK than the extra mana.  :)<br><br>Kahntun<br>58 Shadow Knight<br>RoA GL<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
